Dirk Lotriet(Shutterstock) (Shutterstock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein - The rape case against the owner of a popular Bloemfontein sports pub was postponed to September 9 after a brief appearance in&nbsp;the Bloemfontein Regional Court on Tuesday. The 46-year-old man faces charges of rape and human trafficking. He is out on R5 000 bail. The bail conditions imposed on him were extended. He must report to the Navalsig police station every Tuesday and Thursday, and he is forbidden to contact state witnesses.A 23-year-old employee claims she was raped in the toilet of one of the the pubs. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.